            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Though I am not sure why this is needed, since it should be set automatically to the `root_dir` if I am correct (which should be found by `root_markers`?):\n\nfrom `:help lsp` : \n\n```\n      â€¢ {cmd_cwd}?             (`string`, default: cwd) Directory to launch\n                               the `cmd` process. Not related to `root_dir`.\n```\n\n`nvim-lspconfig/lua/lspconfig/manager.lua` is irrelevant, not used for `vim.lsp.config`.\n\nregarding this:\n\n```\nvim.lsp.config('sorbet', {\n  cmd_cwd = vim.fs.root(0, 'Gemfile')\n})\n```\n\nthat `cmd_cwd` will be evaluated *once*, and depends on whatever random buffer might be open. it's not evaluated for each buffer.",
