            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk There is similar issue with `ast_grep`: it either should be run inside project dir (which won't happens when we run nvim in one project's dir and later open a file from another project) or get extra `--config /another/project/sgconfig.yml` args.\n\nHow this can be fixed? This won't work (probably because it's too late and `cmd` is already executed):\n```lua\n        before_init = function(_, config)\n            config.cmd_cwd = config.root_dir\n        end,\n```\n\nI've also tried to modify `cmd_cwd` on `BufEnter` but it looks like this has no effect. Probably original `cwd_cwd` is cached/copied somewhere and later calls to `vim.lsp.config()` has no effect. Here is what I tried:\n\n```lua\n            vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufEnter', {\n                group = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup('user.lsp.bufenter', { clear = true }),\n                pattern = '*',\n                callback = function(ev)\n                    vim.lsp.config(\n                        'ast_grep',\n                        { cmd_cwd = vim.fs.dirname(vim.fs.abspath(ev.file)) }\n                    )\n                end,\n            })\n```\n\nI've even tried to `:lcd` on `BufEnter` - does not work either. `:pwd` shows `:lcd` works okay, but `ast-grep` still executes in directory where `nvim` was started.",
