            "body": "There is no good way of defining a dynamic `cmd_cwd` in a \"config\". The plan is perhaps https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32287#issuecomment-2835155023\n\nMeanwhile, doing it like this:\n\n```\nvim.lsp.config('sorbet', {\n  cmd_cwd = vim.fs.root(0, 'Gemfile')\n})\n```\n\nmay be good enough, assuming you don't request the config until you open a buffer that's in your project.",
