            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I just accidentally found a workaround:\n\n```lua\n    ast_grep = {\n        reuse_client = function(client, config)\n            config.cmd_cwd = config.root_dir\n            return client.config.cmd_cwd == config.cmd_cwd\n        end,\n    },\n```\n\nAt a glance it works just fine: I've tried to open files from different projects in any order, restart vim with auto-sessions plugin and a lot of such opened files - all looks good.\n\nIs this hack looks good/safe to you?",
